ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
0 = neither; 1 = right; 2 = left; 3 = bilateral; blank = Missing Form/Incomplete Workbook

1 = Participant not eligible; 2 = MRI stopped at participant request; 3 = Equipment failure; 4 = Other; 5 = Severe distortion due to metal in knee; 6 = Refused; 7 = Participant did not show for appointment; 8 = Knee with short protocol; 9 = Not available; 10 = Knee not expected per protocol; 11 = Knee not eligible; 12 = Missed visit; 13 = Participant opted for one knee only; 14 = Scanned before thigh protocol started; 19 = Non-exposed control; blank = Missing form/incomplete workbook/Not expected
0=Original OAI Siemens Trio MR used; 1= Alternate Siemens TIM Trio platform used; 2=Upgrade OAI Trio to TIM Trio platform used; blank = Missing form/incomplete workbook/Not expected

Possible values: L AXIAL MPR; L COR IW TSE; L COR MPR; L SAG 3D DESS WE; L SAG IW TSE FS; L SAG T2 MAP; OAI Prescription; R AXIAL MPR; R COR IW TSE; R COR MPR; R SAG 3D DESS WE; R SAG IW TSE FS; R SAG T2 MAP; THIGH T1; L COR T1 3D FLASH WE; R COR T1 3D FLASH WE
N= QCd and found to be unacceptable; NR= QCd unacceptable, chosen for release; Y=QCd and found to be acceptable; YD= Not QCd and accepted by default

ElementDescription: Days between most recent surgery and MRI

Notes: 0= USA Instrument quadrature knee coil used; 1= InVivo 8-channel knee coil; 2=Body Coil used

ElementDescription: Does knee have MRI marker for this scanning session
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes; blank = Missing Form/Incomplete workbook/Not expected/Missing
